---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Text from "@/components/fundations/elements/Text.astro";
import Wrapper from "@/components/fundations/containers/Wrapper.astro";
---

<BaseLayout>
  <section>
    <Wrapper variant="standard" class="py-32">
      <div>
        <Text
          tag="h1"
          variant="displayMD"
          class="text-balance text-accent-500 font-display uppercase leading-tight mt-8"
        >
          About Nova Roma
        </Text>
      </div>
      <Wrapper variant="prose" class="mt-12">
        <p>
          Nova Roma Horizon Innovation Society is a non-profit organization
          conceived as an &quot;innovation sanctuary&quot; dedicated to cultivating
          talent and supporting a broader investment strategy. Our primary mission
          is to foster a safe and encouraging environment where entrepreneurs can
          pursue self-determined paths without the rigid constraints of traditional
          careers. We define innovators as individuals who willingly forego
          stability for the flexibility to remain opportunistic.
        </p>

        <h3>Our Vision</h3>
        <p>
          We aim to be the trusted, local alternative that genuinely invests in
          students and the Canadian ecosystem, actively countering extractive
          models and establishing ourselves as a central hub for innovation. Our
          long-term vision is to develop an &quot;AI-native workforce&quot; and
          support &quot;career innovators&quot; who thrive on flexibility and
          opportunity.
        </p>

        <h3>What We Do – Our Core Pillars</h3>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <strong>Talent Pipeline &amp; AI Workforce Development:</strong>
            We train individuals in strategic, high-demand skills such as business
            process mapping, problem-first research, and the application of
            agentic AI. This initiative is designed to create an &quot;AI-ready&quot;
            workforce for Canadian businesses, addressing the existing gap in AI
            adoption. Through our &quot;timeshare consultant&quot; or &quot;next-gen
            co-op&quot; model, Nova Roma hires and coaches students to serve Small
            and Medium Businesses (SMBs) that require AI process adoption but
            lack internal capabilities.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Flexible Work for Innovators:</strong>
            We provide high-skill, flexible gig work opportunities for
            entrepreneurs. This enables them to engage in paid consulting through
            Nova Roma during slower periods of their own ventures, allowing for a
            seamless transition back to their startups when momentum builds,
            thereby avoiding the all-or-nothing leap often required when leaving a
            traditional 9-to-5 job.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Ecosystem Hub &amp; Channel Partnership:</strong>
            Functioning as a central hub, Nova Roma amplifies communication and
            collaboration across four key domains: Governance (NGOs, think tanks),
            Education (schools, universities), Industry, and Capital. We act as a
            crucial &quot;channel partnership,&quot; enhancing the flow of capital,
            intellectual property, and talent between these vital sectors.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Grant-Leveraged Project Facilitation:</strong>
            We identify fundable opportunities and coordinate
            &quot;off-takers&quot; (organizations that benefit from deployed assets
            or services) for grant-funded projects. By leveraging our non-profit
            status, we can often stack multiple government funds, significantly
            reducing project costs for our partners. Furthermore, we are
            developing AI-powered tools to automate and streamline the grant
            application process, serving both our internal needs and offering this
            as a service to our partners.
          </li>
        </ol>

        <h3>Our Approach to Sustainability</h3>
        <p>
          Nova Roma is designed to be a self-sustaining ecosystem. While
          for-profit entities may operate on the periphery to capture value, our
          core non-profit remains &quot;pure,&quot; managed for the public good.
          Our sustainability is primarily driven by service revenues, such as
          corporate training subscriptions, rather than relying solely on
          donations. We also aim to offer strategic partners access to deal flow
          and innovation in exchange for initial funding, thereby establishing Nova
          Roma as a valuable hub that attracts ongoing engagement and
          subscriptions.
        </p>

        <h3>Commitment to the Canadian Economy</h3>
        <p>
          Ultimately, Nova Roma is dedicated to contributing to a more innovative
          and resilient Canadian economy, embodying long-term, mission-driven goals.
          We aspire to become the primary, trusted player in fostering innovation
          and connecting talent with capital within the Canadian ecosystem.
        </p>
      </Wrapper>
    </Wrapper>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
